00:00:11,368 --> 00:00:22,526
This next idea changes everything,  batch.size (default 16 kilobytes) controls the maximum size of a batch per partition.

5
00:00:22,526 --> 00:00:30,223
linger.ms (default 0) adds a deliberate delay to allow more records to accumulate.

6
00:00:30,223 --> 00:00:41,289
Setting linger.ms=10 can increase batch fill rate dramatically, boosting throughput at the cost of a small latency increase.

